translations.en: Starting Swoole HTTP server on %s:%s at %s %s
translations.bg: Стартиране на Swoole HTTP сървър на %s:%s в %s %s

translations.en: Static serving is enabled and document_root is set to %s
translations.bg: Статичното сервиране на съдържание е активно и document_root е зададен на %s
Дебъг портове за процесите са активни: %s - %s

translations.en: End of startup messages - Swoole server is now serving requests
translations.bg: Край на съобщенията от инициализацията - Swoole сървърът обслужва заявки

translations.en: Invalid option "%s" provided to server configuration.
The Swoole server has the "document_root" option set to "%s" but the "enable_static_handler" is not enabled. To serve static content the "enable_static_handler" setting needs to be enabled.
The Swoole server has the "enable_static_handler" setting enabled but the "document_root" is not configured. To serve static content the "document_root" setting needs to be set.
HTTP2 is enabled but no SSL is configured. ssl_cert_file or ssl_key_file is not set.
The specified SSL certificate file %s is not readable. Please check the filesystem permissions. The file must be readable by the user executing the server.
The specified SSL key file %s is not readable. Please check the filesystem permissions. The file must be readable by the user executing the server.
The "daemonize" option is set but there is no "log_file" option specified.
The specified log_file path %s exists but is not writable. Please check the filesystem permissions. File file must be writable by the user executing the server.

The specified log_file path %s does not exists but can not be created because the directory %s is not writeable. Please check the filesystem permissions. File directory must be writable by the user executing the server.
